 Privacy Policy for PadelBuddy

  Last Updated: December 20, 2024

  Introduction

  PadelBuddy ("we," "our," or "us") is an AI-powered video analysis application for padel sports. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when you use our mobile application.

  Information We Collect

  Account Information

  - Device Identifier: We automatically generate a unique anonymous device ID to identify your account
  - Email Address: If you create an account (optional)
  - Display Name: Your chosen username (optional)

  Video Content

  - Match Videos: Videos you upload for AI analysis
  - Video Metadata: Duration, date uploaded, file size
  - Generated Highlights: Clips created from your uploaded videos
  - Thumbnails: Preview images generated from your videos

  Usage Data

  - App Settings: Your preferences for notifications, video quality, language, and download settings
  - Match History: Records of your uploaded matches and generated highlights

  Subscription Information

  - Purchase Status: Whether you have an active subscription
  - Subscription Type: Monthly or yearly plan (if applicable)

  Note: We do not collect or store your payment card details. All payment processing is handled securely by Apple (App Store) and our subscription management provider, RevenueCat.

  How We Use Your Information

  Video Processing

  Your uploaded videos are processed using:
  - Google Gemini AI: To analyze gameplay and identify highlight-worthy moments (rallies, smashes, saves, etc.)
  - Computer Vision: To detect players and gameplay patterns

  Service Delivery

  - To provide AI-powered video analysis and highlight generation
  - To sync your matches and highlights across sessions
  - To manage your subscription and premium features
  - To send notifications about processing status (with your permission)

  Service Improvement

  - To improve our AI analysis accuracy
  - To optimize app performance

  Data Storage and Security

  Local Storage

  - iOS Keychain / Android Keystore: Securely stores your authentication credentials using platform encryption
  - Local Database (Hive): Stores match data and settings on your device for offline access

  Server Storage

  - Backend Database: Your match metadata and highlights are stored on our secure servers hosted on Railway
  - Video Processing: Videos are temporarily cached during processing and automatically deleted after analysis is complete

  Security Measures

  - All data transmitted between your device and our servers uses HTTPS encryption
  - Sensitive credentials are stored using platform-native secure storage (iOS Keychain, Android Keystore)
  - Server infrastructure is protected with industry-standard security practices

  Third-Party Services

  We use the following third-party services:

  | Service          | Purpose                                | Privacy Policy                       |
  |------------------|----------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
  | Google Gemini AI | Video analysis and highlight detection | https://policies.google.com/privacy  |
  | RevenueCat       | Subscription management                | https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy   |
  | Apple App Store  | Payment processing                     | https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/ |

  Data Retention

  - Videos: Processed videos are temporarily stored during analysis (typically deleted within 24 hours of processing completion)
  - Highlights: Generated highlight clips are retained until you delete them or your account
  - Account Data: Retained while your account is active
  - Match History: Retained until you delete individual matches or your account

  Your Rights and Choices

  Access and Control

  - View Your Data: Access all your matches and highlights within the app
  - Delete Matches: Remove individual matches and their associated highlights at any time
  - Delete Account: Permanently delete your account and all associated data through Settings > Delete Account

  Notifications

  - You can enable or disable notifications in the app settings
  - Processing status notifications are optional

  Data Export

  - You can save generated highlights to your device's photo library

  Children's Privacy

  PadelBuddy is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately.

  International Data Transfers

  Your data may be processed on servers located outside your country of residence. By using PadelBuddy, you consent to the transfer of your information to facilities outside your jurisdiction.

  Changes to This Policy

  We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material changes by:
  - Posting the new Privacy Policy in the app
  - Updating the "Last Updated" date

  Your continued use of PadelBuddy after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

  Contact Us

  If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:

  Email: harrythentrepreneur@gmail.com

  Developer: Harry Edwards

  ---
  California Privacy Rights (CCPA)

  If you are a California resident, you have the right to:
  - Know what personal information we collect
  - Request deletion of your personal information
  - Opt-out of the sale of your personal information (Note: We do not sell personal information)

  European Privacy Rights (GDPR)

  If you are in the European Economic Area, you have rights including:
  - Access to your personal data
  - Correction of inaccurate data
  - Deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten")
  - Data portability
  - Objection to processing

  To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information above.
